    "description": "Join the TransIndia Logistics South Asia Partners family as a Warehouse Manager in Chandigarh. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout TransIndia Logistics South Asia Partners:\nTransIndia Logistics South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Coordinate with customer service teams to resolve delivery issues\n• Optimize delivery routes to reduce cost and improve efficiency\n• Ensure compliance with transportation regulations and safety standards\n• Implement warehouse management systems (WMS) and track KPIs\n• Implement cost-saving initiatives in transportation and warehousing\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Freight Forwarding\n• Proficiency in Data Analytics\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in SAP SCM\n• Proficiency in WMS\n• Proficiency in Fleet Management\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in 3PL Management\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Flexible working hours\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chandigarh, Punjab, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with TransIndia Logistics South Asia Partners!",
